radiographic_examinations.findings: Bilateral mild atelectasis, small pericardial effusion, decreased attenuation of the liver compatible with fatty deposition, calcified gallstone within the gallbladder neck, small amount of pericholecystic fluid, multiple bilateral renal hypodensities likely representing cysts, hypodense structure in the right adnexa, smaller hypodensity in the left ovary, moderate degenerative changes along lower thoracic and lumbar spine.
